public interface BaseOpsInt

Title: BaseOpsInt

Description:

BaseOps interface class We use interface classes to lay a framework for other classes which intend to inherit the base traits of this class. Since each instance will have different methods based on the data structure we do not write the body of the function, instead when the class inherits baseopsint it is required to write the core functions.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Sam R. Thangiah
